xcmCommsEngineMIB.name: xcmCommsEngineMIB
xcmCommsEngineMIB.description: Version: 2.32.pub The MIB module for detailed protocol stack graphing, and active management of communications protocol stacks, communications end system applications, communications intermediate systems, and communications gateways for network accessible host systems. Usage: Note that throughout this MIB module, the INDEX clauses referring to 'hrDeviceIndex' for the 'hrDeviceTable' (Devices Group) of the Host Resources MIB (RFC 1514) shall ALWAYS specify host system CPUs (ie, 'hrDeviceProcessor') and shall NOT specify ANY other 'hrDeviceType'. Usage: The object 'xcmCommsStackXrefHrCommDevIndex' in the Comms Stack Xref Group of this MIB MAY be used to specify (for 'bottom' protocol stack layers) the corresponding value of 'hrDeviceIndex' for network, modem, serial port, and parallel port devices. And the object 'xcmCommsStackXrefIfIndex' may be used to specify the value of 'ifIndex' for the corresponding entry in the MIB-II 'ifTable' (ie, 'network interfaces'). Copyright (C) 1997 Xerox Corporation. All Rights Reserved.

xcmCommsEngineTable.name: xcmCommsEngineTable
xcmCommsEngineTable.description: A table of the communications engines installed and (possibly) running on platforms (ie, CPUs) on this host system.

xcmCommsEngineEntry.name: xcmCommsEngineEntry
xcmCommsEngineEntry.description: An entry for a communications engine installed and (possibly) running on a platform (ie, CPU) on this host system. Usage: Note that values of 'hrDeviceIndex' used to reference entries in the 'xcmCommsEngineTable' shall ALWAYS reference entries in the 'hrDeviceTable' with 'hrDeviceType' equal to 'hrDeviceProcessor' (representing host system CPUs and therefore also having corresponding entries in the 'hrProcessorTable').

xcmCommsEngineRowStatus.name: xcmCommsEngineRowStatus
xcmCommsEngineRowStatus.description: This object is used to create and delete individual conceptual rows in the 'xcmCommsEngineTable'.

xcmCommsEngineName.name: xcmCommsEngineName
xcmCommsEngineName.description: Human-readable name, used by system administrators and end users to identify this communications engine for systems management. Usage: This name should be the one normally used in a command shell for control of this communications engine.

xcmCommsEngineStackLast.name: xcmCommsEngineStackLast
xcmCommsEngineStackLast.description: The last entry index (regardless of its current state) in the 'xcmCommsStackTable' of this communications engine, on this host system. Usage: The last entry index explicitly bounds the valid range of 'xcmCommsStackIndex'.

xcmCommsEngineMuxLast.name: xcmCommsEngineMuxLast
xcmCommsEngineMuxLast.description: The last entry index (regardless of its current state) in the 'xcmCommsMuxTable' of this communications engine, on this host system. Usage: The last entry index explicitly bounds the valid range of 'xcmCommsMuxIndex'.

xcmCommsEngineAddressLast.name: xcmCommsEngineAddressLast
xcmCommsEngineAddressLast.description: The last entry index (regardless of its current state) in the 'xcmCommsAddressTable' of this communications engine, on this host system. Usage: The last entry index explicitly bounds the valid range of 'xcmCommsAddressIndex'.

xcmCommsEngineMgmtLast.name: xcmCommsEngineMgmtLast
xcmCommsEngineMgmtLast.description: The last entry index (regardless of its current state) in the 'xcmCommsMgmtTable' of this communications engine, on this host system. Usage: The last entry index explicitly bounds the valid range of 'xcmCommsMgmtIndex'.

xcmCommsEngineGroupSupport.name: xcmCommsEngineGroupSupport
xcmCommsEngineGroupSupport.description: The terse conformance statement of ALL mandatory, conditionally mandatory, and optional XCMI Comms Engine MIB object groups supported by this management agent implementation (ie, version) on this host system, specified in a bit-mask. Usage: Conforming management agents shall ALWAYS accurately report their support for XCMI Comms Engine MIB object groups.

xcmCommsEngineCreateSupport.name: xcmCommsEngineCreateSupport
xcmCommsEngineCreateSupport.description: The terse conformance statement of ALL mandatory, conditionally mandatory, and optional XCMI Comms Engine MIB object groups supported for dynamic row creation (via '...RowStatus') by this management agent implementation (ie, version) on this host system, specified in a bit-mask. Usage: Conforming management agents shall ALWAYS accurately report their support for XCMI Comms Engine MIB object groups.

xcmCommsEngineUpdateSupport.name: xcmCommsEngineUpdateSupport
xcmCommsEngineUpdateSupport.description: The terse conformance statement of ALL mandatory, conditionally mandatory, and optional XCMI Comms Engine MIB object groups supported for existing row update (via SNMP Set-Request PDUs) by this management agent implementation (ie, version) on this host system, specified in a bit-mask. Usage: Conforming management agents shall ALWAYS accurately report their support for XCMI Comms Engine MIB object groups.

xcmCommsEngineExtTable.name: xcmCommsEngineExtTable
xcmCommsEngineExtTable.description: A 'sparse' table which augments 'xcmCommsEngineTable' with additional useful information.

xcmCommsEngineExtEntry.name: xcmCommsEngineExtEntry
xcmCommsEngineExtEntry.description: A 'sparse' entry which augments 'xcmCommsEngineEntry' with additional useful information.

xcmCommsEngineExtRowStatus.name: xcmCommsEngineExtRowStatus
xcmCommsEngineExtRowStatus.description: This object is used to create and delete individual conceptual rows in the 'xcmCommsEngineExtTable'.

xcmCommsEngineExtState.name: xcmCommsEngineExtState
xcmCommsEngineExtState.description: A relatively generic description of the current state of this communications entity.

xcmCommsEngineExtConditions.name: xcmCommsEngineExtConditions
xcmCommsEngineExtConditions.description: A relatively generic description of the current conditions of this communications entity.

xcmCommsEngineExtVersionID.name: xcmCommsEngineExtVersionID
xcmCommsEngineExtVersionID.reference: See: 'hrSW[Installed|Run]ID' in the Software Installed and Software Running groups of the IETF HR MIB (RFC 1514).
xcmCommsEngineExtVersionID.description: The software product ID of the SNMP sub-agent which implements the XCMI Comms Engine MIB on this host system. Usage: This object shall specify the software product ID of an SNMP sub-agent (possibly also found in a conceptual row in the 'hrSWRunTable' and/or 'hrSWInstalledTable' in the IETF HR MIB). This object shall NOT specify a particular release of the XCMI Comms Engine MIB, or the whole host system product. Note: Contrast with 'sysObjectID' for the whole SNMP agent in the IETF MIB-II (RFC 1213) and 'hrDeviceID' for the whole device (or whole product, in the case of 'xcmHrDevice...') in the IETF Host Resources MIB (RFC 1514).

xcmCommsEngineExtVersionDate.name: xcmCommsEngineExtVersionDate
xcmCommsEngineExtVersionDate.reference: See: 'hrSW[Installed|Run]ID' in the Software Installed and Software Running groups of the IETF HR MIB (RFC 1514).
xcmCommsEngineExtVersionDate.description: The software build date of the SNMP sub-agent which implements the XCMI Comms Engine MIB on this host system. Usage: This object shall specify the BUILD date of the SNMP sub-agent software (not available elsewhere in IETF/XCMI MIBs). This object shall NOT specify the INSTALL date of the SNMP sub-agent software on this host system, nor the RESET date. Note: Contrast with 'hrSWInstalledDate' in the Software Installed group of the IETF Host Resources MIB (RFC 1514), and 'xcmHrDevInfoResetDate' in the Device Info group of the XCMI Host Resources Extensions MIB.

xcmCommsEngineExtMgmtIndex.name: xcmCommsEngineExtMgmtIndex
xcmCommsEngineExtMgmtIndex.description: The value of 'xcmCommsMgmtIndex' corresponding to a directly associated conceptual row in the 'xcmCommsMgmtTable', or zero if this 'managed entity' does NOT require such information.

xcmCommsEngineExtOwnerOID.name: xcmCommsEngineExtOwnerOID
xcmCommsEngineExtOwnerOID.description: The OID (object identifier) of the conceptual row or simple object which represents some 'owner entity' associated with this entry in the 'xcmCommsEngineExtTable'.

xcmCommsStackTable.name: xcmCommsStackTable
xcmCommsStackTable.description: A table containing information on the relationships between the multiple stack layers or sublayers (ie, protocol entities) comprising the (possibly) running 'protocol stacks' on this host system. In particular, it contains information about which stack layer runs 'above' and 'below' which other stack layer.

xcmCommsStackEntry.name: xcmCommsStackEntry
xcmCommsStackEntry.description: An entry for a stack layer in a protocol stack installed and (possibly) running on this host system.

xcmCommsStackIndex.name: xcmCommsStackIndex
xcmCommsStackIndex.description: A unique value used by this host system to identify this conceptual row in the 'xcmCommsStackTable'.

xcmCommsStackRowStatus.name: xcmCommsStackRowStatus
xcmCommsStackRowStatus.description: This object is used to create and delete individual conceptual rows in the 'xcmCommsStackTable'.

xcmCommsStackTypeOID.name: xcmCommsStackTypeOID
xcmCommsStackTypeOID.description: An unambiguous stack layer type, used by system administrators and end users to identify the type of this stack layer. Usage: Since this unambiguous stack layer type is specified as an object identifier, it may be taken from any IETF, Xerox, third- party, or product-specific MIB, or it may simply be any IETF SMIv2-style 'autonomous type'. Usage: Suitable values for this unambiguous stack layer type are specified in the companion XCMI Comms Config TC (eg, 'xcmCONetwareIPX').

xcmCommsStackName.name: xcmCommsStackName
xcmCommsStackName.description: Human-readable name, used by system administrators and end users to identify this stack layer for systems management. Usage: This name should be the one normally used in a command shell for control of this stack layer.

xcmCommsStackPosition.name: xcmCommsStackPosition
xcmCommsStackPosition.description: A relatively generic description of the current position of this protocol entity (ie, this layer) in this protocol stack. Usage: A conceptual row in 'xcmCommsStackTable', which occupies a 'bottom' position in a protocol stack AND has a corresponding row in the 'xcmCommsStackXrefTable', should ALWAYS have valid references in 'xcmCommsStackXrefIfIndex' (to IETF MIB-II) and 'xcmCommsStackXrefHrCommDevIndex' (to IETF Host Resources MIB). Usage: A conceptual row in 'xcmCommsStackTable' which occupies a 'lowerMux' and/or an 'upperMux' position in a protocol stack shall ALWAYS have one (or two) valid corresponding conceptual rows in the 'xcmCommsMuxTable', as the conventionally used 'xcmCommsStack[Lower|Upper]StackIndex' objects take on zero values for multiplexors (thus breaking the graph of the stack layers, without the use of the 'xcmCommsMuxTable').

xcmCommsStackLowerStackIndex.name: xcmCommsStackLowerStackIndex
xcmCommsStackLowerStackIndex.description: The value of 'xcmCommsStackIndex' corresponding to a next lower associated conceptual row in the 'xcmCommsStackTable', or zero if this stack layer's position is either 'bottom' or 'lowerMux'.

xcmCommsStackUpperStackIndex.name: xcmCommsStackUpperStackIndex
xcmCommsStackUpperStackIndex.description: The value of 'xcmCommsStackIndex' corresponding to a next higher associated conceptual row in the 'xcmCommsStackTable', or zero if this stack layer's position is either 'upperMux' or sometimes 'top' (see usage note below). Usage: Only for protocol entities whose current purpose is either 'layerInterWorkingUnit' (ie, relays or gateways) or 'systemInterWorkingUnit' (ie, application gateways), it is permitted that the stack layer whose current position is 'top' have an upper layer index pointing to the peer entity (also in a 'top' position) which comprises the 'other half' of a relay or gateway between two different address domains (ie, an active protocol conversion relay) - that is the graphed protocol stack is an inverted 'U'.

xcmCommsStackAddressIndex.name: xcmCommsStackAddressIndex
xcmCommsStackAddressIndex.description: The value of 'xcmCommsAddressIndex' corresponding to the first associated conceptual row in the 'xcmCommsAddressTable', or zero if this 'owner entity' does NOT require such information.

xcmCommsStackOptionIndex.name: xcmCommsStackOptionIndex
xcmCommsStackOptionIndex.description: The value of 'xcmCommsOptionIndex' corresponding to the first associated conceptual row in the 'xcmCommsOptionTable', or zero if this stack layer does NOT require such information.

xcmCommsStackLowerMuxIndex.name: xcmCommsStackLowerMuxIndex
xcmCommsStackLowerMuxIndex.description: The value of 'xcmCommsMuxIndex' corresponding to the first associated conceptual row in the 'xcmCommsMuxTable', or zero if this stack layer's position is NOT 'lowerMux'.

xcmCommsStackUpperMuxIndex.name: xcmCommsStackUpperMuxIndex
xcmCommsStackUpperMuxIndex.description: The value of 'xcmCommsMuxIndex' corresponding to the first associated conceptual row in the 'xcmCommsMuxTable', or zero if this stack layer's position is NOT 'upperMux'.

xcmCommsStackExtTable.name: xcmCommsStackExtTable
xcmCommsStackExtTable.description: A 'sparse' table which augments 'xcmCommsStackTable' with additional useful information.

xcmCommsStackExtEntry.name: xcmCommsStackExtEntry
xcmCommsStackExtEntry.description: A 'sparse' entry which augments 'xcmCommsStackEntry' with additional useful information.

xcmCommsStackExtRowStatus.name: xcmCommsStackExtRowStatus
xcmCommsStackExtRowStatus.description: This object is used to create and delete individual conceptual rows in the 'xcmCommsStackExtTable'.

xcmCommsStackExtState.name: xcmCommsStackExtState
xcmCommsStackExtState.description: A relatively generic description of the current state of this communications entity.

xcmCommsStackExtConditions.name: xcmCommsStackExtConditions
xcmCommsStackExtConditions.description: A relatively generic description of the current conditions of this communications entity.

xcmCommsStackExtPurpose.name: xcmCommsStackExtPurpose
xcmCommsStackExtPurpose.description: A relatively generic description of the current purpose of this stack layer during normal operation.

xcmCommsStackExtRole.name: xcmCommsStackExtRole
xcmCommsStackExtRole.description: A relatively generic description of the current role of this stack layer during normal operation.

xcmCommsStackExtSuite.name: xcmCommsStackExtSuite
xcmCommsStackExtSuite.description: The current protocol suite of this protocol entity (stack layer or sublayer).

xcmCommsStackExtSuiteVersion.name: xcmCommsStackExtSuiteVersion
xcmCommsStackExtSuiteVersion.description: The current protocol suite version of this protocol entity (stack layer or sublayer).

xcmCommsStackExtLayer.name: xcmCommsStackExtLayer
xcmCommsStackExtLayer.description: The closest approximate layer in the OSI Reference Model (CCITT X.200 | ISO 7498) to the current behavior of this stack layer or sublayer.

xcmCommsStackExtProtocol.name: xcmCommsStackExtProtocol
xcmCommsStackExtProtocol.description: The specific protocol (within a given protocol suite) currently configured for this stack layer or sublayer.

xcmCommsStackExtMgmtIndex.name: xcmCommsStackExtMgmtIndex
xcmCommsStackExtMgmtIndex.description: The value of 'xcmCommsMgmtIndex' corresponding to the directly associated conceptual row in the 'xcmCommsMgmtTable', or zero if this 'managed entity' does NOT require such information.

xcmCommsStackExtOwnerOID.name: xcmCommsStackExtOwnerOID
xcmCommsStackExtOwnerOID.description: The OID (object identifier) of the conceptual row or simple object which represents some 'owner entity' associated with this entry in the 'xcmCommsStackExtTable'. Usage: A Printer Channel, for example, might choose to specify the OID of some conceptual row in the 'prtChannelTable'.

xcmCommsStackXrefTable.name: xcmCommsStackXrefTable
xcmCommsStackXrefTable.description: A table containing optional cross reference information for the multiple stack layers or sublayers (ie, protocol entities) comprising the (possibly) running 'protocol stacks' on this host system.

xcmCommsStackXrefEntry.name: xcmCommsStackXrefEntry
xcmCommsStackXrefEntry.description: An entry for a stack layer in a protocol stack installed and (possibly) running on this host system.

xcmCommsStackXrefRowStatus.name: xcmCommsStackXrefRowStatus
xcmCommsStackXrefRowStatus.description: This object is used to create and delete individual conceptual rows in the 'xcmCommsStackXrefTable'.

xcmCommsStackXrefLayerMgmtIndex.name: xcmCommsStackXrefLayerMgmtIndex
xcmCommsStackXrefLayerMgmtIndex.description: The value of 'xcmCommsStackIndex' corresponding to the one-to-one associated conceptual row in the 'xcmCommsStackTable' which has 'xcmCommsStackExtPurpose' of 'layerManagement', or zero if this this stack layer has no associated layer management entity.

xcmCommsStackXrefLayerSecIndex.name: xcmCommsStackXrefLayerSecIndex
xcmCommsStackXrefLayerSecIndex.description: The value of 'xcmCommsStackIndex' corresponding to the one-to-one associated conceptual row in the 'xcmCommsStackTable' which has 'xcmCommsStackExtPurpose' of 'layerSecurity', or zero if this this stack layer has no associated layer security entity.

xcmCommsStackXrefLayerIWUIndex.name: xcmCommsStackXrefLayerIWUIndex
xcmCommsStackXrefLayerIWUIndex.description: The value of 'xcmCommsStackIndex' corresponding to the one-to-one associated conceptual row in the 'xcmCommsStackTable' which has 'xcmCommsStackExtPurpose' of 'layerInterWorkingUnit', or zero if this this stack layer has no associated layer relay entity.

xcmCommsStackXrefHrSWRunIndex.name: xcmCommsStackXrefHrSWRunIndex
xcmCommsStackXrefHrSWRunIndex.description: The value of 'hrSWRunIndex' corresponding to the directly associated conceptual row in the 'hrSWRunTable' of the Host Resources MIB (RFC 1514), or zero if 'hrSWRunTable' is NOT implemented.

xcmCommsStackXrefHrSWInsIndex.name: xcmCommsStackXrefHrSWInsIndex
xcmCommsStackXrefHrSWInsIndex.description: The value of 'hrSWInstalledIndex' corresponding to the directly associated conceptual row in the 'hrSWInstalledTable' of the Host Resources MIB (RFC 1514), or zero if 'hrSWInstalledTable' is NOT implemented.

xcmCommsStackXrefIfIndex.name: xcmCommsStackXrefIfIndex
xcmCommsStackXrefIfIndex.reference: See: 'xcmCommsStackPosition' and the 'InterfaceIndex' textual convention in Evolution of the Interfaces Group of MIB-II (RFC 1573).
xcmCommsStackXrefIfIndex.description: The value of 'ifIndex' corresponding to the directly associated conceptual row in the 'ifTable' (Interfaces Group) of the MIB-II (RFC 1213), or zero if the position of this stack layer is NOT 'bottom' (ie, this stack layer does NOT represent a physical 'network interface'). Usage: This is partially a convenience object, since given the value of 'hrDeviceIndex' for an 'hrDeviceNetwork' type device, the corresponding 'ifIndex' is found in the mandatory entry in the 'hrNetworkTable'. However, note that for 'hrDeviceModem', 'hrDeviceSerialPort', and 'hrDeviceParallelPort' devices, the 'xcmCommsStackXrefIfIndex' object is a NECESSITY for support of this communications engine MIB.

xcmCommsStackXrefHrCommDevIndex.name: xcmCommsStackXrefHrCommDevIndex
xcmCommsStackXrefHrCommDevIndex.reference: See: 'xcmCommsStackPosition' and the 'hrDeviceIndex' of the Devices Group of the Host Resources MIB (RFC 1514).
xcmCommsStackXrefHrCommDevIndex.description: The value of 'hrDeviceIndex' corresponding to the directly associated conceptual rows in the 'hrDeviceTable' and (possibly) 'hrNetworkTable' of the Host Resources MIB (RFC 1514), or zero if the position of this stack layer is NOT 'bottom' (ie, this stack layer does NOT represent a physical 'network interface'). Usage: Note that for 'hrDeviceModem', 'hrDeviceSerialPort', and 'hrDeviceParallelPort' devices, there is NO corresponding entry in the 'hrNetworkTable', a subtle difference between MIB-II (RFC 1213) and the Host Resources MIB (RFC 1514).

xcmCommsMuxTable.name: xcmCommsMuxTable
xcmCommsMuxTable.description: A table containing information on the relationships between the multiple stack layers or sublayers (ie, protocol entities) participating in a 'upper' or 'lower' multiplexor (ie, the simultaneous adjacency of two or more 'upper' or 'lower' stack layers with a single instance of a 'base' stack layer), eg, IP (a 'base' stack layer) operating below both TCP and UDP (the 'adjacent' stack layers).

xcmCommsMuxEntry.name: xcmCommsMuxEntry
xcmCommsMuxEntry.description: An entry for a 'base' stack layer participating in an 'upper' or 'lower' multiplexor.

xcmCommsMuxIndex.name: xcmCommsMuxIndex
xcmCommsMuxIndex.description: A unique value used by this host system to identify this conceptual row in the 'xcmCommsMuxTable'.

xcmCommsMuxRowStatus.name: xcmCommsMuxRowStatus
xcmCommsMuxRowStatus.description: This object is used to create and delete individual conceptual rows in the 'xcmCommsMuxTable'.

xcmCommsMuxNextIndex.name: xcmCommsMuxNextIndex
xcmCommsMuxNextIndex.description: The value of 'xcmCommsMuxIndex' corresponding to a next associated conceptual row in the 'xcmCommsMuxTable', or zero if this is the last associated conceptual row in a given set.

xcmCommsMuxPreviousIndex.name: xcmCommsMuxPreviousIndex
xcmCommsMuxPreviousIndex.description: The value of 'xcmCommsMuxIndex' corresponding to a previous associated conceptual row in the 'xcmCommsMuxTable', or zero if this is the first associated conceptual row in a given set.

xcmCommsMuxOptionIndex.name: xcmCommsMuxOptionIndex
xcmCommsMuxOptionIndex.description: The value of 'xcmCommsOptionIndex' corresponding to the first associated conceptual row in the 'xcmCommsOptionTable', or zero if this multiplexor entry does NOT require such information.

xcmCommsMuxBaseStackIndex.name: xcmCommsMuxBaseStackIndex
xcmCommsMuxBaseStackIndex.description: The value of 'xcmCommsStackIndex' corresponding to the base associated conceptual row in the 'xcmCommsStackTable'.

xcmCommsMuxAdjacentStackIndex.name: xcmCommsMuxAdjacentStackIndex
xcmCommsMuxAdjacentStackIndex.description: The value of 'xcmCommsStackIndex' corresponding to the adjacent associated conceptual row in the 'xcmCommsStackTable'.

xcmCommsMuxExtTable.name: xcmCommsMuxExtTable
xcmCommsMuxExtTable.description: A 'sparse' table which augments 'xcmCommsMuxTable' with additional useful information.

xcmCommsMuxExtEntry.name: xcmCommsMuxExtEntry
xcmCommsMuxExtEntry.description: A 'sparse' entry which augments 'xcmCommsMuxEntry' with additional useful information.

xcmCommsMuxExtRowStatus.name: xcmCommsMuxExtRowStatus
xcmCommsMuxExtRowStatus.description: This object is used to create and delete individual conceptual rows in the 'xcmCommsMuxExtTable'.

xcmCommsMuxExtState.name: xcmCommsMuxExtState
xcmCommsMuxExtState.description: A relatively generic description of the current state of this communications entity.

xcmCommsMuxExtConditions.name: xcmCommsMuxExtConditions
xcmCommsMuxExtConditions.description: A relatively generic description of the current conditions of this communications entity.

xcmCommsMuxExtMgmtIndex.name: xcmCommsMuxExtMgmtIndex
xcmCommsMuxExtMgmtIndex.description: The value of 'xcmCommsMgmtIndex' corresponding to the directly associated conceptual row in the 'xcmCommsMgmtTable', or zero if this 'managed entity' does NOT require such information.

xcmCommsMuxExtAddressIndex.name: xcmCommsMuxExtAddressIndex
xcmCommsMuxExtAddressIndex.description: The value of 'xcmCommsAddressIndex' corresponding to the first associated conceptual row in the 'xcmCommsAddressTable', or zero if this 'owner entity' does NOT require such information.

xcmCommsMuxExtOwnerOID.name: xcmCommsMuxExtOwnerOID
xcmCommsMuxExtOwnerOID.description: The OID (object identifier) of the conceptual row or simple object which represents some 'owner entity' associated with this entry in the 'xcmCommsMuxExtTable'.

xcmCommsAddressTable.name: xcmCommsAddressTable
xcmCommsAddressTable.description: A table containing information on unicast, multicast, and broadcast addresses (remote/local) known to this host system.

xcmCommsAddressEntry.name: xcmCommsAddressEntry
xcmCommsAddressEntry.description: An entry containing information on one unicast, multicast, or broadcast address (remote/local) known to this host system.

xcmCommsAddressIndex.name: xcmCommsAddressIndex
xcmCommsAddressIndex.description: A unique value used by this host system to identify this conceptual row in the 'xcmCommsAddressTable'.

xcmCommsAddressRowStatus.name: xcmCommsAddressRowStatus
xcmCommsAddressRowStatus.description: This object is used to create and delete individual conceptual rows in the 'xcmCommsAddressTable'.

xcmCommsAddressTypeOID.name: xcmCommsAddressTypeOID
xcmCommsAddressTypeOID.description: An unambiguous address type, used by system administrators and end users to identify the type of this address. Usage: Since this unambiguous address type is specified as an object identifier, it may be taken from any IETF, Xerox, third- party, or product-specific MIB, or it may simply be any IETF SMIv2-style 'autonomous type'. Usage: Suitable values for this unambiguous address type are specified in the companion XCMI Comms Config TC (eg, 'xcmCONetwareIPX').

xcmCommsAddressUserRole.name: xcmCommsAddressUserRole
xcmCommsAddressUserRole.reference: See: 'XcmSecUserRole' in the XCMI Security/AAA TC. See: 'xcmDevHelpCommsAddressIndex' in the XCMI Host Resources Extensions MIB.
xcmCommsAddressUserRole.description: An unambiguous address user role, used by system administrators and end users to identify the user role of this address. Usage: This unambiguous address user role is specified by a value defined in the textual convention 'XcmSecUserRole' in the XCMI Security/AAA TC. Usage: This unambiguous address user role is weakly typed here to avoid cyclic compilation dependencies between XCMI MIBs. Usage: A chain of 'xcmCommsAddressEntry' objects may be pointed to by 'xcmDevHelpCommsAddressIndex' in the Device Help group of the XCMI Host Resources Extensions MIB. In this case, the 'xcmCommsAddressTypeOID' object may contain values such as 'xcmCOOsiwanPSTNAddress' (analog phone number), 'xcmCOOsiwanFaxAddress' (fax phone number), etc, taken from the XCMI Comms Config TC. In this case, the 'xcmCommsAddressUserRole' object may be used to specify the role of the system admin, system operator, etc (whose name is specified by 'xcmCommsAddressName', address format is specified by 'xcmCommsAddressTypeOID', and actual address is specified by 'xcmCommsAddressCanonical').

xcmCommsAddressName.name: xcmCommsAddressName
xcmCommsAddressName.description: Human-readable name, used by system administrators and end users to identify this protocol entity. Usage: This name should be the one normally used in a command shell for control of this protocol entity. Usage: When a chain of 'xcmCommsAddressEntry' objects is pointed to by 'xcmHrDevHelpCommsAddressIndex' in the Device Help group of the XCMI Host Resources Extensions MIB (see details at 'xcmCommsAddressUserRole' object above) special semantics apply. In this case, the 'xcmCommsAddressName' object may be used to specify the name of the system admin, system operator, etc (whose role is specified by 'xcmCommsAddressUserRole', address format is specified by 'xcmCommsAddressTypeOID', and actual address is specified by 'xcmCommsAddressCanonical').

xcmCommsAddressCanonical.name: xcmCommsAddressCanonical
xcmCommsAddressCanonical.description: The current canonical address of this protocol entity.

xcmCommsAddressNextIndex.name: xcmCommsAddressNextIndex
xcmCommsAddressNextIndex.description: The value of 'xcmCommsAddressIndex' corresponding to a next associated conceptual row in the 'xcmCommsAddressTable', or zero if this is the last associated conceptual row in a given set. Usage: A locally administered 'directory' may be searched and/or managed via use of the 'xcmCommsAddressNextIndex' and the 'xcmCommsAddressPreviousIndex' objects referenced from each base protocol entity (ie, stack layer).

xcmCommsAddressPreviousIndex.name: xcmCommsAddressPreviousIndex
xcmCommsAddressPreviousIndex.description: The value of 'xcmCommsAddressIndex' corresponding to a previous associated conceptual row in the 'xcmCommsAddressTable', or zero if this is the first associated conceptual row in a given set.

xcmCommsAddressOptionIndex.name: xcmCommsAddressOptionIndex
xcmCommsAddressOptionIndex.description: The value of 'xcmCommsOptionIndex' corresponding to the first associated conceptual row in the 'xcmCommsOptionTable', or zero if this address entry does NOT require such information.

xcmCommsAddressExtTable.name: xcmCommsAddressExtTable
xcmCommsAddressExtTable.description: A 'sparse' table which augments 'xcmCommsAddressTable' with additional useful information.

xcmCommsAddressExtEntry.name: xcmCommsAddressExtEntry
xcmCommsAddressExtEntry.description: A 'sparse' entry which augments 'xcmCommsAddressEntry' with additional useful information.

xcmCommsAddressExtRowStatus.name: xcmCommsAddressExtRowStatus
xcmCommsAddressExtRowStatus.description: This object is used to create and delete individual conceptual rows in the 'xcmCommsAddressExtTable'.

xcmCommsAddressExtState.name: xcmCommsAddressExtState
xcmCommsAddressExtState.description: A relatively generic description of the current state of this communications entity.

xcmCommsAddressExtConditions.name: xcmCommsAddressExtConditions
xcmCommsAddressExtConditions.description: A relatively generic description of the current conditions of this communications entity.

xcmCommsAddressExtForm.name: xcmCommsAddressExtForm
xcmCommsAddressExtForm.description: The current address form of this protocol entity.
